[],"created_at":1784392745104737001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py` is 805 LOC — 5 over the 800 soft cap — and is grandfathered on the module-size allowlist (ceiling 806). Graduate it off the allowlist by splitting it along a cohesive call-graph seam: the hand-maintained Jira->local field/status translation layer, which is a self-contained cluster with no dependency on the code left behind.\n\nNote on the architecture.md record: the offenders-table remedy row for this file is STALE — it names a target module `inbound_status.py` and a function `_jira_status_to_local` that do NOT exist in the current code (verified: grep finds neither). This ticket does NOT rely on that row for its rationale; it chooses the seam on the code's current structure and DELETES the stale row as part of graduating the file.\n\n## What\n\nExtract the self-contained Jira->local *translation* cluster into a new leaf module `inbound_fields.py` (same package). Moved symbols (a cohesive cluster whose bodies reference only each other — the new module imports nothing that stays behind):\n- `_load_adf` (+ `_ADF_KEY_INBOUND`, `_AdfModule_Inbound`)\n- translation maps `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_TYPE`, `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_PRIORITY`, `_JIRA_TO_LOCAL_STATUS`, `_REBAR_STATUS_LABEL_TO_LOCAL`\n- `_extract_jira_field_value`, `_assignee_matches`, `_normalize_jira_body`, `_map_jira_to_local_fields`\n\n`inbound_differ.py` imports these back from `inbound_fields` and RE-EXPORTS them (so `inbound_differ.<symbol>` attribute access and the config/parity tests keep resolving). The scalar-field diff (`_diff_jira_vs_local`), sub-entity diffs (`_diff_comments_inbound`/`_diff_links_inbound`/`_diff_labels_inbound`), `_EXCLUDED_PREFIXES`, `_load_link_direction`, `_OUTBOUND_TO_INBOUND_FIELD`, `_build_outbound_context`, and `compute_inbound_mutations` all STAY. Pure refactor — no behavior change, no signature change.\n\nThen graduate the file off the gate: remove its row from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` AND `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and delete its (stale) remedy row in `docs/architecture.md`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `inbound_fields.py` exists, is between 100 and 800 LOC, and contains the moved translation cluster (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py`)\n- [ ] `inbound_differ.py` is <= 800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py`)\n- [ ] `inbound_differ.py` is absent from BOTH `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`, and its `docs/architecture.md` remedy row is deleted (verify: `! grep inbound_differ .github/module-size-allowlist.txt .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py` passes (verify: `pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`)\n- [ ] The reconciler test suite is green with no behavior change (verify: `pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler -q`)\n- [ ] Backward compatibility preserved: `inbound_differ._map_jira_to_local_fields`, `inbound_differ._JIRA_TO_LOCAL_STATUS`, `inbound_differ._assignee_matches`, `inbound_differ._normalize_jira_body` still resolve as module attributes (re-exported)\n\n## Notes\nLanded as its own Gerrit change (LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1) before the ticket is closed. Refactor is mechanical/behavior-preserving, so E5 testing-plan is not-applicable (existing reconciler tests are the oracle).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py","reason":"new leaf module holding the extracted Jira->local translation cluster"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py","reason":"shrink below 800 LOC; import+re-export moved symbols"},{"path":".github/module-size-allowlist.txt","reason":"remove inbound_differ.py membership row"},{"path":".github/module-size-ceilings.txt","reason":"remove inbound_differ.py ceiling row"},{"path":"docs/architecture.md","reason":"delete inbound_differ.py remedy row from the offenders table"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","716f-b917-9fc8-41f5"]],"parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_status_uuid":"4e20c770-8a74-4d66-aafb-fc0dff0af7f6","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["module-size"],"ticket_id":"a130-2b7c-429c-43d1","ticket_type":"story","title":"Split inbound_differ.py: extract Jira->local translation into inbound_fields.py","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["91cf71a3-acc5-4e49-a59f-c2a916bd9ec1","6c240437-daee-476b-80a6-99fa5d5b472c","c9882027-0ab5-41b8-8c02-6865af5926d8","a1064cad-95b3-4aa6-8d58-fcc6448d28c9","4e20c770-8a74-4d66-aafb-fc0dff0af7f6","4a6342ce-8713-4dbc-88f7-b875317fd7de","ade0c65f-54e7-46a4-b1f7-fe7e52e977ce"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784396836670851611,"uuid":"2a3bcb1f-16ba-4ea9-a6b7-cba6c874a872"}